{
  "texts": [
    "It is worth mentioning that an MoS 2 -based threshold switching memristor is reported to handle up to 10 6 pulses.It is worth noting that these performance metrics are based on an individual device.",
    "However, challenges still remain when integrating them into an artificial neuron network, in which the devices fabricated so far are in the scale of µm 2, which should be reduced for high-density integration.",
    "Recently, Hao et al.",
    "successfully demonstrated the realization of a network of artificial neurons using 2D planar MoS 2 [15].",
    "Their devices utilized TiW and Ag electrodes patterned on a single crystal monolayer MoS 2 to act as the postsynaptic and presynaptic terminals, respectively."
  ]
}